OL,6,FCllr Galley said he asked the council
OL,7,Fwhether there would be support for the
OL,8,Fcreation of a Tramtown Steering Group
OL,9,Fwith volunteer representation,
OL,10,Fallowing it to become part of the
OL,11,FBlackpool Heritage Museum Trust, but
OL,12,Fhe said he hasn't had an answer on
OL,13,Fthis.
OL,15,FGalley also said the tram shed which
OL,16,Fstores Blackpool's heritage trams has
OL,17,Fwrongly been described as "warm and
OL,18,Fdry" by the leadership, when it is
OL,19,Factually damp and has a leaking roof,
OL,20,Fputting the trams themselves at risk
OL,21,Fof deterioration.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
